---

## 1. Purpose

This FAQ answers common questions about the OPRMT™ Framework, the repository structure, usage expectations, documentation standards, prompt submissions, standard changes, and related systems such as Prompt Compliance Engineering and DOAS™.

This document is intended for readers, contributors, maintainers, learners, and approved implementation partners.

---

## 2. What Is OPRMT™?

OPRMT™ is a structured prompt engineering framework created by Michael W. Fleming.

The framework organizes prompts and AI instructions through five controlled components:

```text
O — Objective
P — Parameters
R — Results
M — Method
T — Tools
```

The purpose of OPRMT™ is to make prompts more structured, repeatable, auditable, and suitable for professional implementation.

---

## 3. What Does OPRMT™ Stand For?

OPRMT™ stands for:

| Letter | Component | Meaning |
|---|---|---|
| O | Objective | Defines the task, goal, or outcome the prompt must accomplish |
| P | Parameters | Defines inputs, constraints, boundaries, variables, and operating conditions |
| R | Results | Defines the expected output, deliverable, format, or success criteria |
| M | Method | Defines the execution process, reasoning structure, or workflow |
| T | Tools | Defines allowed tools, resources, systems, files, or integrations |

---

