---

## 6. Is OPRMT™ a Prompt Library or a Framework?

OPRMT™ is primarily a framework.

A prompt library may be built using OPRMT™, but the framework itself defines the structure and rules for prompt construction.

A prompt library is a collection of prompt assets. OPRMT™ is the structured system used to design, classify, evaluate, and govern those assets.

---

## 7. What Is Prompt Compliance Engineering?

Prompt Compliance Engineering, or PCE, is a discipline associated with validating whether prompts, AI outputs, and structured systems comply with defined requirements, constraints, formatting rules, operational standards, and intended use.

Within the OPRMT™ ecosystem, PCE helps evaluate whether prompt outputs follow the assigned Objective, Parameters, Results, Method, and Tools.

---

## 8. What Is DOAS™?

DOAS™ refers to a scoring and assessment concept used to evaluate prompt or output quality against structured criteria.

In the OPRMT™ ecosystem, DOAS™ may be used to score prompt compliance, output completeness, execution quality, and alignment with framework requirements.

DOAS™ documentation should not claim guaranteed success rates unless supported by validated testing, controlled metrics, and approved language.

---

## 9. Can I Use OPRMT™ for My Own Prompts?

Personal, educational, and internal reference use may be allowed under the repository license and usage guidance.

Commercial use, redistribution, white-labeling, certification claims, and resale may require written permission or a separate license.

Review the following files before using OPRMT™ materials:

```text
/LICENSE.md
/NOTICE.md
/legal/COMMERCIAL_USE_GUIDANCE.md
/legal/USAGE_POLICY.md
```

---

## 10. Can I Sell OPRMT™ Prompt Packs?

Not by default.

Selling OPRMT™ prompt packs, copied templates, derivative prompt clusters, training materials, or commercial products based substantially on OPRMT™ repository content may require written permission from the owner.

Commercial use must follow the repository license, notice, and commercial use guidance.

---

## 11. Can I Teach OPRMT™?

You may reference or discuss OPRMT™ for educational purposes with proper attribution, subject to repository terms.

You may not claim to be an official OPRMT™ instructor, authorized certification provider, accredited training partner, or official representative unless approved in writing.

