---

## 17. What File Naming Style Should Be Used?

Use clear, readable, hyphenated filenames.

Preferred examples:

```text
OPRMT-Framework-Standard-v1.0.md
OPRMT-Objective-Spec-v1.0.md
PCE-Validation-Taxonomy-v1.0.md
DOAS-Scoring-Model-v1.0.md
```

Avoid:

```text
final.md
newfile.md
copy.md
doc1.md
updated-final-final.md
```

---

## 18. What Metadata Should Major Documents Include?

Major documents should include a metadata block or visible header containing:

```text
Title
Repository
Owner
Document Type
Version
Status
Recommended Path
Last Updated
Usage Scope
```

Formal specification files may use YAML front matter where appropriate.

