## 19. What Is the Difference Between `/docs`, `/standard`, and `/framework`?

| Folder | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `/docs` | General documentation, guides, glossary, FAQ, getting started materials |
| `/standard` | Official framework standards, controlled definitions, versioned specifications |
| `/framework` | Component-level documentation for Objective, Parameters, Results, Method, and Tools |

---

## 20. What Is the Difference Between OPRMT™ and PCE?

OPRMT™ is the structured prompt framework.

PCE is the validation and compliance discipline used to evaluate whether prompts and outputs satisfy defined rules, constraints, and standards.

OPRMT™ defines structure. PCE validates adherence to structure and requirements.

---

## 21. What Is the Difference Between PCE and DOAS™?

PCE refers to the compliance engineering discipline.

DOAS™ refers to a scoring or assessment model that may be used within or alongside PCE.

PCE asks whether an output complies. DOAS™ can help score how well it complies.

---

## 22. Can OPRMT™ Guarantee Better AI Outputs?

No repository document should claim guaranteed results, guaranteed profitability, legal compliance, academic recognition, employment outcomes, or universal accuracy.

OPRMT™ is designed to improve structure, clarity, repeatability, and auditability. Performance depends on task quality, model behavior, data quality, user inputs, tool access, and review standards.

